Metasoma pyriform in lateral view (
Fig. 1
), slightly compressed laterally; petiole (metasomal segments 1-2 ) elongate and slender, 2.7 times as long as maximum width; T 1 and T 2 mostly polished, shiny and smooth, except for median part of T 2 with fine, superficial and sparse punctures; T 3 -T 7 polished-punctate, with very fine, superficial and dense punctures, except for lateral part of each tergite; ovipositor 1.7 times as long as length of fore wing, and 4.4 times as long as length of hind tibia (
Fig. 1
